1
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:14,030
What's so great about Gao Baihan?

2
00:00:14,030 --> 00:00:15,800
I hope his flight gets delayed.

3
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,130
People cut in line when he boards.

4
00:00:17,130 --> 00:00:18,200
He gets diarrhea while boarding.

5
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,370
And there's no toilet paper.

6
00:00:19,370 --> 00:00:21,130
He can't find a taxi after landing.

7
00:00:21,130 --> 00:00:22,330
He's going to study abroad, right?

8
00:00:22,330 --> 00:00:23,700
So I hope he gets...

9
00:00:25,070 --> 00:00:26,000
Ostracized by his classmates.

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,230
Disliked by his professors.

11
00:00:27,230 --> 00:00:28,800
Forgets to save his thesis.

12
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:29,970
And can't graduate.

13
00:00:30,670 --> 00:00:32,470
Why are you cursing him?

14
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:34,470
He didn't mean it.

15
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:36,970
Strange.

16
00:00:36,970 --> 00:00:38,630
We haven't actually broken up.

17
00:00:38,630 --> 00:00:40,530
It's already over.

18
00:00:40,530 --> 00:00:42,070
From now on, my birthday wish every year

19
00:00:42,070 --> 00:00:43,430
Will be for you,

20
00:00:43,430 --> 00:00:44,630
Lin Liying.

21
00:00:44,630 --> 00:00:47,090
That you'll never run into Gao Baihan again.

22
00:00:51,670 --> 00:00:54,200
What if I want to see him?

23
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,370
What are you doing?

24
00:01:02,370 --> 00:01:04,800
Heartbroken and still stealing my food?

25
00:01:15,030 --> 00:01:19,289
I forgot to make a wish. Do you have any more of those popping candies you like?

26
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:23,300
You must have missed these snacks.

27
00:01:23,970 --> 00:01:25,270
Yes, indeed.

28
00:01:28,270 --> 00:01:29,430
Cheers.

29
00:01:29,430 --> 00:01:30,470
Thanks.

30
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,330
You've been in America for about 10 years now.

31
00:01:34,729 --> 00:01:35,870
Pretty much.

32
00:01:35,870 --> 00:01:37,300
Yes, it's been 10 years.

33
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,600
Are you married?

34
00:01:39,330 --> 00:01:40,930
Three times already.

35
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:43,370
Three times.

36
00:01:47,930 --> 00:01:49,330
What are you laughing at?

37
00:01:49,330 --> 00:01:51,130
You're talking nonsense.

38
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:53,229
I'm not married.

39
00:01:53,229 --> 00:01:54,800
I can't believe it.

40
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:56,470
You're handsome.

41
00:01:56,470 --> 00:01:58,200
And successful in your career.

42
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,930
How could you possibly not have a girlfriend?

43
00:01:59,930 --> 00:02:00,800
Tell me.

44
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:01,570
Why?

45
00:02:02,170 --> 00:02:03,700
Is it because of a divorce?

46
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:04,530
Cheating,

47
00:02:04,530 --> 00:02:05,430
getting caught,

48
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:06,670
kicked out...

49
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,270
What?

50
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,900
Actually, all these years

51
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,760
there's been someone in my heart.

52
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:23,070
Don't use such a lame line.

53
00:02:23,070 --> 00:02:24,630
Lin Liying, don't listen.

54
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:25,930
If you're going to talk about Lin Liying,

55
00:02:25,930 --> 00:02:27,570
this script is terrible.

56
00:02:27,570 --> 00:02:28,930
It's you.

57
00:02:39,970 --> 00:02:41,170
Jiang Zhihao.

58
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:44,370
The person in my heart all these years

59
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,900
has always been you.

60
00:02:56,070 --> 00:02:57,400
I told you

61
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,770
he would fall for it.

62
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:02,900
Lin Liying.

63
00:03:03,470 --> 00:03:05,500
Why do you always take his side?

64
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,070
Have you forgotten

65
00:03:07,070 --> 00:03:08,670
how upset you were back then?

66
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:10,300
Let me tell you,

67
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:12,070
people need to learn to grow up.

68
00:03:12,070 --> 00:03:12,970
Gao Bohan,

69
00:03:12,970 --> 00:03:14,630
I don't love you anymore.

70
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:15,830
Go love him instead.

71
00:03:15,830 --> 00:03:17,600
Love him, kiss him,

72
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,329
shut him up with your lips.

73
00:03:19,329 --> 00:03:21,030
Go away.

74
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:22,370
Jiang Zhihao, go away.

75
00:03:22,370 --> 00:03:23,300
Don't come near me. Jiang Zhihao, what are you doing?

76
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:24,870
Don't come near me. Kiss him.

77
00:03:24,870 --> 00:03:26,600
Kiss him. Do it.

78
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:27,930
One kiss won't hurt.

79
00:03:27,930 --> 00:03:28,800
Hurry up.

80
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:31,300
Jiang Zhihao! Lin Liying, take him away!

81
00:05:24,130 --> 00:05:25,700
That's for Dad.

82
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:26,930
Dad left early this morning.

83
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:28,200
You're spacing out.

84
00:05:33,530 --> 00:05:34,700
Jiang Zhihao.

85
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:38,170
Don't you think Dad's been acting strange lately?

86
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:41,500
Dad seems pretty normal to me.

87
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:44,630
No, that's just it. He's too normal.

88
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:47,800
You know what Niu Yifei told me the other day?

89
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,930
What?

90
00:05:48,930 --> 00:05:50,800
He said he saw Dad taking the bus.

91
00:05:52,970 --> 00:05:53,870
I've seen him for several days

92
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:55,900
waiting for the bus.

93
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,200
He takes the bus every day.

94
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,270
That's right.

95
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,230
He asked how to get to the car wash

96
00:06:05,230 --> 00:06:07,330
and wanted me to teach him how to take the bus.

97
00:06:07,330 --> 00:06:08,370
Then I casually asked him

98
00:06:08,370 --> 00:06:10,470
if he wanted to apply for a senior citizen card.

99
00:06:10,470 --> 00:06:12,230
Turns out he's not even 65 yet!

100
00:06:12,930 --> 00:06:14,330
He looks way older than his age.

101
00:06:14,330 --> 00:06:15,700
Right?

102
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:19,100
You're saying my dad takes the bus to the car wash?

103
00:06:19,930 --> 00:06:20,930
He goes to wash cars?

104
00:06:20,930 --> 00:06:22,330
That's right.

105
00:06:22,330 --> 00:06:24,500
You know your father's hobby?

106
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:25,630
Now he's

107
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:26,900
living frugally.

108
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:28,200
He has money.

109
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,530
Money and people.

110
00:06:29,530 --> 00:06:31,000
What do you think he can do?

111
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:50,200
Mr. Jiang.

112
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:52,870
Want to come join us?

113
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,230
You guys go ahead.

114
00:07:20,530 --> 00:07:21,830
What you see here

115
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:24,100
are all the co-branding partners we're currently negotiating with.

116
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:24,870
That means

117
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:27,030
this proposal uses a dual co-branding approach

118
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:28,700
to collaborate with Panda Airways.

119
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,600
We'll handle everything this time

120
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,370
and try our best to meet all your requirements.

121
00:07:32,370 --> 00:07:34,130
We've also secured Mr. Baimu.

122
00:07:34,130 --> 00:07:35,570
We approached him ourselves,

123
00:07:35,570 --> 00:07:38,630
but he wasn't interested in commercial partnerships.

124
00:07:38,630 --> 00:07:39,630
Really?

125
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:41,730
It seems

126
00:07:41,730 --> 00:07:43,970
the power of good food works wonders.

127
00:07:43,970 --> 00:07:45,970
We've already spoken with Mr. Baimu.

128
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:48,030
He says he's a fan of our Nuo Toast

129
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:49,800
and really enjoys our products,

130
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:52,030
so he's willing to collaborate.

131
00:07:54,170 --> 00:07:56,230
I've actually never tried Nuo Toast.

132
00:07:57,230 --> 00:08:00,170
Based on our last meeting,

133
00:08:00,170 --> 00:08:02,200
the collaboration is as good as done,

134
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,260
no backing out now.

135
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,270
What I mean is,

136
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:08,170
I don't plan to collaborate with Nuo Toast.

137
00:08:08,170 --> 00:08:11,030
No plans to work with Nuo Toast.

138
00:08:12,870 --> 00:08:14,130
If it's Mr. Baimu,

139
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:15,870
we would be very interested.

140
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:16,970
That's great!

141
00:08:16,970 --> 00:08:18,970
So what Deputy Director Huang means is

142
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:21,830
we can start drafting the contract and proceed with the process.

143
00:08:21,830 --> 00:08:22,570
What I'm saying is,

144
00:08:22,570 --> 00:08:25,770
if you can secure Mr. Baimu,

145
00:08:25,770 --> 00:08:28,100
then things should go smoothly from here.

146
00:08:28,730 --> 00:08:29,430
Okay.

147
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,930
After that,

148
00:08:30,930 --> 00:08:33,260
I'll have Liying schedule a time with you.

149
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,130
Alright.

150
00:08:42,299 --> 00:08:43,370
Shanru.

151
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:48,870
Sales are down this week.

152
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:50,800
The Qingcheng store is closed too.

153
00:08:51,230 --> 00:08:52,470
Got it.

154
00:08:52,470 --> 00:08:53,630
The items on the shelf weren't baked today.

155
00:08:53,630 --> 00:08:54,630
Take them all down.

156
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:56,870
Make sure customers get everything at its freshest.

157
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,300
Yes, understood.

158
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,330
Shanru.

159
00:09:11,330 --> 00:09:13,630
I might not have been clear this morning.

160
00:09:13,630 --> 00:09:14,670
But last night,

161
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:17,170
Mr. Baimu clearly rejected me.

162
00:09:17,170 --> 00:09:18,430
Do you know something?

163
00:09:20,230 --> 00:09:22,200
The sales figures from last month and this month

164
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,730
are worlds apart.

165
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:26,500
A few months ago,

166
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:29,500
Fang Nuo was still a loving husband who adored his wife.

167
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,670
And now?

168
00:09:31,570 --> 00:09:33,100
In this world,

169
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,630
the only constant truth

170
00:09:34,630 --> 00:09:36,700
is that everything changes.

171
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:40,470
Gao Bohan didn't want to cooperate yesterday,

172
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:43,130
but that doesn't mean he won't want to today or tomorrow.

173
00:09:43,130 --> 00:09:45,370
Whatever method or means necessary,

174
00:09:45,370 --> 00:09:47,300
we need to change his mind. I can't think of...

175
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,970
Invite him to the company for a meeting.

176
00:09:48,970 --> 00:09:50,570
The sooner the better.

177
00:09:50,570 --> 00:09:53,100
Use your senior-junior relationship.

178
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:55,470
Beg if you have to, but get him here.

179
00:09:58,170 --> 00:09:59,400
Beg?

180
00:10:00,930 --> 00:10:02,100
I'm really...

181
00:10:02,770 --> 00:10:04,630
not good at begging.

182
00:10:04,630 --> 00:10:05,700
Do I need to...

183
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:14,900
You're not working today?

184
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:16,330
And you can even cook?

185
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:19,470
I took two hours off.

186
00:10:19,470 --> 00:10:20,900
I thought

187
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:23,530
it should be my turn to cook once in a while.

188
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:33,130
Dad.

189
00:10:33,130 --> 00:10:34,900
You've been leaving early and coming home late.

190
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,300
What have you been doing?

191
00:10:41,330 --> 00:10:43,130
It's not what you think.

192
00:10:43,130 --> 00:10:44,600
I haven't been gambling.

193
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:49,000
Really, I haven't been gambling.

194
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,230
I just found a simple job.

195
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:53,130
Thought I'd save some money.

196
00:10:53,130 --> 00:10:55,070
Just in case we need it for emergencies.

197
00:10:55,070 --> 00:10:56,800
It's more reassuring that way.

198
00:11:00,070 --> 00:11:02,100
We know.

199
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,770
We've seen it all.

200
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,330
You've been following me?

201
00:11:20,470 --> 00:11:21,900
Actually,

202
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,630
that car wash job

203
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:25,670
isn't that hard.

204
00:11:25,670 --> 00:11:26,970
It's tiring, sure,

205
00:11:26,970 --> 00:11:28,700
but I get paid in cash every day.

206
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,230
It's very satisfying.

207
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:31,600
And also,

208
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,170
I can build my muscles.

209
00:11:33,170 --> 00:11:34,670
I'm not bragging, look.

210
00:11:35,370 --> 00:11:36,970
My muscles are showing now.

211
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,900
I wish your mom could feel them.

212
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:47,400
Besides,

213
00:11:49,430 --> 00:11:52,230
your little stall doesn't make much money either.

214
00:11:53,270 --> 00:11:54,670
Your mom is gone.

215
00:11:54,670 --> 00:11:56,470
The beauty salon

216
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:58,530
doesn't bring in any income anymore.

217
00:11:59,070 --> 00:12:00,930
But don't worry.

218
00:12:00,930 --> 00:12:02,470
See?

219
00:12:02,470 --> 00:12:04,030
I'm in good shape.

220
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:05,370
No need to worry.

221
00:12:07,370 --> 00:12:09,030
Life must go on.

222
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:10,100
Eat.

223
00:12:21,970 --> 00:12:24,400
Have you thought about going back to your job?

224
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,830
Not at all.

225
00:12:25,830 --> 00:12:27,030
But wait,

226
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:28,670
you were doing fine at your job.

227
00:12:28,670 --> 00:12:30,070
Then suddenly you wanted to do your own thing.

228
00:12:30,070 --> 00:12:32,230
You wanted to open your own breakfast shop.

229
00:12:32,230 --> 00:12:34,030
I already did.

230
00:12:35,070 --> 00:12:36,530
That's hardly a breakfast shop.

231
00:12:36,530 --> 00:12:38,800
Just a tiny stall.

232
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:39,470
And you're so full of yourself,

233
00:12:39,470 --> 00:12:41,100
making those so-called 'limited editions.'

234
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:42,700
How much can you really make?

235
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:45,170
Dad's so old now.

236
00:12:45,170 --> 00:12:47,430
He's gone from being childish to mature.

237
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,930
If you want, open a real breakfast shop.

238
00:12:50,930 --> 00:12:52,600
A proper store.

239
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,070
Right, Weiyu?

240
00:12:54,070 --> 00:12:55,200
What?

241
00:12:56,170 --> 00:12:58,730
I told him to open his own shop.

242
00:13:01,070 --> 00:13:02,170
If you're not going back to Linlin,

243
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:04,830
then of course it's better to open your own shop.

244
00:13:04,930 --> 00:13:07,000
But have you really made up your mind?

245
00:13:10,770 --> 00:13:12,530
If Mom were still here,

246
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:15,490
what do you think she would want you to do?

247
00:14:37,970 --> 00:14:40,270
Founder of renowned premium toast chain.

248
00:14:40,270 --> 00:14:41,830
After his extramarital affair was exposed,

249
00:14:41,830 --> 00:14:43,530
his business has taken a significant hit.

250
00:14:43,530 --> 00:14:45,600
Besides the three directly-operated stores closed this month,

251
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,100
the co-branded products with breakfast shops

252
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:49,630
are also reportedly experiencing poor sales.

253
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:52,870
Lin Liying.

254
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:54,370
Come out and look at this!

255
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,270
This...

256
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:57,900
Is this your company?

257
00:14:59,530 --> 00:15:00,830
Will we not get paid?

258
00:15:09,130 --> 00:15:10,230
What's wrong?

259
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:33,070
Why are you here so early?

260
00:15:33,070 --> 00:15:34,200
It suddenly started pouring.

261
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,330
Yeah.

262
00:15:35,330 --> 00:15:38,590
My colleagues went out for lunch and haven't returned yet.

263
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:39,600
Did I come too early?

264
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,430
Have you eaten?

265
00:15:40,430 --> 00:15:41,500
I can get something for you.

266
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,430
I haven't eaten yet.

267
00:15:43,430 --> 00:15:45,830
I was preparing materials for our meeting.

268
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:47,370
Meeting?

269
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:53,500
I'm leaving.

270
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,000
Hold on, please!

271
00:15:57,270 --> 00:15:59,700
Who said the boss is Mr. Baimu's fan?

272
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:00,930
That part is true.

273
00:16:00,930 --> 00:16:02,000
And that today is her birthday?

274
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,170
And wanted to give her a special surprise?

275
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:04,370
That part is false.

276
00:16:04,370 --> 00:16:05,670
I even bought special gifts.

277
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:06,730
To help you save face.

278
00:16:06,730 --> 00:16:08,900
That's really thoughtful of you.

279
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,130
I'm a bit upset.

280
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:17,070
Don't think of it as a meeting.

281
00:16:17,070 --> 00:16:19,270
Just sit down and listen to a brief presentation.

282
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:20,630
Have some afternoon tea.

283
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:22,000
How does that sound?

284
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,070
No.

285
00:16:23,930 --> 00:16:25,630
How did you get hurt? Did I...

